# Turboexec Museum Combine

This set of scripts utilizes Xenos' turboexec package system to create a museum combine script that operates efficeintly using turboexec

The script automatically moves all elements of a specific type into the inventory, then levels them up to a user specified target tier, then moves all the stones back and clears the inventory

All of this happens within 2 frames, however due to the resource intensive nature of this task it will likely take 1-2 seconds. However, I believe this is still the fastest way by far to get your stones leveled

This script does clear stones after it finishes, and while I have never run into any bugs with it clearing valuable stones, that is a potential possibility. Exercise caution when using the script, as I cannot test for all edge cases.

# Usage 

The only parts of this script the user should edit are found inside 'launch museum combine'
This consists of three variables
1. `String element`
    * Set this to the element of the powerstones which you would like to level up
2. `int targetTier`
    * Set this to the tier of stone which you would like to reach. Once stones reach this level or higher, they will be moved back into equipped
3. `int maxBuyTier`
    * Set this to the maximum tier of stone to purchace from the offshore market. This is used to prevent you from accidentally spending all of your cubes
    * Note: If the script moves all your stones but doesn't do anything else, make sure this is high enough to purchace from the market!

# In Game Requirements

This script requires that you have the Offshore Market exotic skill purchaced, as well as have a fully leveled Museum. Additionally, this script works best with an excess of cubes. Running out of cubes during operation will cause the script to wait until you gain more, which will most likely take a while. Take care to ensure you have an adequate stock of cubes before running.

This script also requires 22 AI lines, which is obtained by maxing out RAM on all servers in the HQ
